# AprilAlgo — Cursor agent rules (v0.3 development)

## Isolation (black-box modules)

- Do **not** read or reason from source files under `src/aprilalgo/indicators/` or `src/aprilalgo/backtest/` when working from **v0.1 / v0.2** context or when the task only needs integration contracts.
- Treat those directories as **black boxes** that satisfy **`docs/DATA_SCHEMA.md`**. Use that file and public entrypoints (CLI, config, strategy APIs) instead of opening every `.py` file.

## No look-ahead

- **Strictly enforce:** no future-dated bars or future information may influence feature generation, confluence, strategy actions, or label construction at decision time *t*.
- Features at *t* use data ≤ *t*. Triple-barrier labels use price path **after** *t* only as defined by the barrier method, never mixing pre-label future into features.

## API / token optimization

- **Before** writing code that touches columns or types, open **`docs/DATA_SCHEMA.md`** and align names and semantics.
- Prefer **narrow context**: attach **specific files** (e.g. one strategy module, `DATA_SCHEMA.md`) instead of broad whole-repo searches when possible.

## Documentation loop

- After a task that changes behavior, conventions, or project direction, update **`CLAUDE.md`** (project context) and/or **`AGENTS.md`** (agent coding rules) so they stay accurate.
- For schema or pipeline contracts, keep **`docs/DATA_SCHEMA.md`** in sync when the interface changes.
